You are working on Ruby Rental, a production-ready rental management SaaS built with Next.js 15 App Router, TypeScript and Supabase.

Rules:

- Never rewrite the architecture.
- Reuse existing components before creating new ones.
- Prefer updating existing files instead of creating duplicates.
- Follow the existing folder structure.
- Use AppShell for all authenticated pages.
- Use the existing UI components from components/ui.
- Keep TypeScript strict. Do not use any.
- Prefer small focused changes.
- Follow the existing service pattern inside services/.
- All database access must go through Supabase.
- Preserve multi-tenant workspace isolation.
- Never remove existing functionality unless explicitly requested.
- Before creating a new component, check whether one already exists.
- Keep styling consistent with the current design system.
- Use existing Button, Modal, Input, Select, Textarea, Badge, Card, FilterBar and PageHeader components whenever possible.
- If fixing an error, modify only the files necessary.
- Explain your plan before making large changes.
